---

**Why only `records` is used for DataFrames**

```
orient='records' → [ {row1}, {row2}, {row3} ]  ✅ use this
                   easy to loop in UI
                   easy to rebuild with pd.DataFrame(data)

orient='dict'    → { col: { index: value } }   ❌ don't use
                   UI has to restructure it

orient='list'    → { col: [val1, val2] }        ❌ don't use
                   harder to loop row by row in UI
```

`records` is the only orient that gives you **one complete row per item** — which is exactly what the UI needs to display a table and what `pd.DataFrame()` needs to reconstruct the data on the server side.
